<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>CySER Summer Workshop 2026 · Web Security CTF</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <div class="brand brand-lg">
        <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
        <div>
          <div class="brand-name">CySER</div>
          <div class="brand-tag">Summer Workshop 2026</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1>Engagement: Skyway Airlines</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        You're a junior pentester at CySER. Skyway Airlines hired the team to audit their web stack.
        Eight findings to confirm. Roughly an hour. Plan your report.
      </p>
      <div class="scoreboard">
        <span class="score-label">Findings Confirmed</span>
        <span class="score-number" id="score"><%= solved.length %></span>
        <span class="score-total">/ <%= total %></span>
        <div class="progress-bar">
          <div class="progress-fill" style="width: <%= (solved.length / total * 100) %>%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <br>
      <a href="/reset" class="reset-btn">Reset Engagement</a>
    </header>

    <div class="engagement-banner">
      <strong>Briefing.</strong>
      Skyway's CTO gave you scope: customer portal, staff tools, internal services. Every challenge below is a
      <em>finding</em>. A real vulnerability class that lives somewhere in the company's surface. Open each, read
      the day's story, exploit the bug, claim the <code>flag{...}</code>.
    </div>

    <div class="challenges-grid">

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch1') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge">Recon</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 1 · First Impressions</h3>
        <p>Skyway's customer portal renders nothing sensitive. Or does it? Source code is your first stop on every engagement.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: Information disclosure in HTML</p>
        <a href="/challenge/1" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch2') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge">AuthZ</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 2 · Bronze to Platinum</h3>
        <p>Skyway's loyalty perks gate on a client-side cookie. The Platinum Lounge has a comp code. Go get it.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: Client-side trust / cookie tampering</p>
        <a href="/challenge/2" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch3') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge">AuthZ</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 3 · The VIP Manifest</h3>
        <p>Customer service has a booking lookup. It does no authorization check. Find the VIP record nobody wanted you to see.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR)</p>
        <a href="/challenge/3" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch4') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge sqli">Injection</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 4 · The Crew Login</h3>
        <p>The crew portal login was written in raw, unparameterized SQL by a contractor. Walk straight past it.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: SQL Injection (auth bypass)</p>
        <a href="/challenge/4" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch5') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge xss">XSS</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 5 · Polluted Search</h3>
        <p>Skyway's search bar reflects your query straight into the page. Marketing's promo code lives in a cookie. Reach in and take it.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: Reflected XSS + cookie exfiltration</p>
        <a href="/challenge/5" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch6') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge ssrf">SSRF</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 6 · The Image Proxy</h3>
        <p>The customer-service tool fetches preview images server-side. It adds an internal auth header. There's an internal admin endpoint that wants exactly that header.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)</p>
        <a href="/challenge/6" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch7') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge llm">LLM</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 7 · The Chatbot Says Too Much</h3>
        <p>Skyway shipped an AI helper. It was instructed never to share the maintenance override. Convince it anyway.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: Prompt Injection / system-prompt leak</p>
        <a href="/challenge/7" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="challenge-card <%= solved.includes('ch8') ? 'solved' : '' %>">
        <div class="card-badge auth">Auth</div>
        <div class="card-difficulty">⭐⭐⭐⭐</div>
        <h3>Day 8 · The Final Boss</h3>
        <p>Ground crew portal hands out JWTs. The verifier has one classic misconfig. Walk in as admin.</p>
        <p class="hint-text">Vuln: JWT alg:none</p>
        <a href="/challenge/8" class="play-btn">Open finding →</a>
      </div>

    </div>

    <footer>
      <p>Every flag follows the format: <code>flag{...}</code></p>
      <p>Stuck on one? Skip and come back. Most findings are independent.</p>
      <p style="margin-top: 12px; opacity: 0.55;">CySER Summer Workshop 2026 · Skyway Airlines engagement</p>
    </footer>
  </div>

  <script>
    const solved = <%= solved.length %>;
    const total = <%= total %>;
    if (solved === total) {
      document.querySelector('.subtitle').textContent =
        'Engagement complete. All ' + total + ' findings confirmed. Time to write the report.';
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
